Results.ReviewText: I'm dismayed that someone has messed with my favourite coffee.. I've drunk almost nothing else but gold blend for half a lifetime, but suddenly someone has negated one of the best things about a quality instant coffee, in that you can drain the cup completely. This is no longer the case & I now have to beware of getting a mouthful of 'grits' like it's a pretend "real" coffee. If I'm going to have to put up with this, I might as well fill the machine & make a pot of fresh coffee anyway.. Would have been a lot better if you had introduced this as a new alternative product, rather than a replacement of your best-known brand with something inferior..
Results.Title: Grit in my cup

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks for getting in touch & letting us know! It's sad to hear you're not liking the changes but we appreciate your feedback.

Results.ReviewText: Crikey I thought it was just us that hated the new stuff but I’ve stumbled on so many like minded unhappy customers. The taste is definitely weaker and if you add more then you get more black sludge in the bottom, not nice at all. As so may have said they do not like this sludge and so many times you try and explain about the micro granules etc, well what we are saying we don’t care what it is, we don’t like it and we dont want it. Please change it back so we can enjoy and your product again or lose so many loyal customers. What is worth noting is that many of the  reviewers giving a positive feedback have received the product for free.
Results.Title: Poor poor poor

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, it really saddens us to hear about your disappointment with the change in recipe but thank you for letting us know! We really appreciate your feedback.

Results.ReviewText:
We have drunk Gold Blend for more years than I can remember and have never found a better instant or fresh coffee that comes close to the rich deep flavour.  Yes, it has always been expensive but what cost for good coffee, even after starting a family and money was tight we always had Gold Blend.
The taste and flavour is now thin, cheap and bitter, I suggest the name is changed to Gold Bland.
We will buy Gold Blend again if the recipe reverts to the original, until then, we will be trying other manufacturers coffee to see if anyone is producing one that is close to our preferred taste.
Devastated to have to say “goodbye Gold Blend and goodbye Nescafe”
Results.Title: Rename to Gold Bland

ClientResponses.Response: It's really sad to hear you're not enjoying the new recipe but thank you very much for taking the time & leave your feedback! We appreciate everyones' comments & will be passing them to the rest of the team!

Results.ReviewText: I've been drinking Gold Blend as long as I can remember - and I'm in my fifties. After realising that I wasn't enjoying the latest jar, I found myself here. OMG, OMG, what have you done? This is the most upset I've been about a product in many many years. Gold Blend was simply one of life's standard benchmarks that you could always rely on. You have now completely ruined things. It's a very unsettling feeling to e.g. walk back into the house and realise you can no longer enjoy a good cup of coffee. Both at home, and at work (office syndicate) we will not be buying any more. Please reconsider and bring back the original version!
Results.Title: OMG - What Have you Done?

ClientResponses.Response: Hey, thank you for getting in touch with us. That's roast and ground coffee at the bottom of your mug! It's nothing to be alarmed about and its actually a sign of quality coffee. After testing many recipes with our consumers, this recipe was the one they loved the most. We're really disappointed to hear you are not enjoying it, however we have added roast and ground coffee ground 10 times finer to give it a more intense aroma whilst maintaining the same smoothness. We are passing all comments onto the team and want to thank you again for the comment.

Results.ReviewText:
I have been enjoying Gold Blend since 1980. For the past few months I have been buying refill packs and recently thought I must have purchased a 'rogue' pack as I didn't experience the lovely aroma when opening the pack, the coffee tasted bland and I was left with grit/powder at the bottom of the mug. Earlier today a friend and fellow (former) Gold Blend fan told me she has stopped buying it as she has been so disappointed with changes made to the product. I decided to search "what has happened to Gold Blend" and have come across all these negative reviews. Please bring back the coffee we all love.
If it ain't broke, don't fix it!!
Results.Title: Why?

ClientResponses.Response:
Hi, thank you for getting in touch & leaving your review!

We're always wanting our consumers to have the best experience, therefore we've added micro ground coffee to our NESCAFÉ Gold Blend to give it a richer aroma and a more intense roasted flavour. 

It saddens us to hear you're not a fan of the new recipe but we really appreciate your feedback & we'll be letting the wider team know!

Results.ReviewText: I have drunk Gold Blend for many years and enjoyed it made with a third heated milk and rest water. Went to buy a new jar recently and was confused b y new packaging but thought it must be the same coffee.. how wrong! Opening the jar there was no aroma like there used to be and it just did not taste the same, it is bitter and leaves a strange taste in the mouth, have tried adding more sugar to no avail. So today i decided to google ‘changes to Gold Blend’ and i discover similar reviews to mine.. your new packaging does not advise changes have been made and i am deeply disappointed in you. Welcome your comments to my review
Results.Title: Why have you changed it?!!!

ClientResponses.Response: It's disappointing to hear you're unhappy with the changes we've made recently but we really appreciate you getting in touch & letting us know your thoughts!

Results.ReviewText:
I've been drinking Nescafé Gold Blend for all of my adult life. I've tried other instants along the way but none have been worth changing to as my main brand.
It's also the only coffee my husband would drink too.
For an instant coffee it was almost as good as a filter coffee, it smelled good when you opened it and then drinking it was a pleasure. Notice I say WAS.
It was all of this until you changed the recipe - now it's just bland, tasteless and there's nasty gritty stuff at the bottom of the cup.
What were you thinking. It's the end of an era.
It's now as poor, not worth drinking so we're back to filter coffee.
Results.Title: You've ruined the best instant coffee out there!

The welcoming aroma has disappeared, the rich taste is no longer there and at the end there is nothing but distasteful dregs.  Please let us know when you go back to the old recipe because we won't be buying anymore in the meantime.
PS  My husband doesn't like it either.

Why change a great product ????

Results.ReviewText: I have been drinking Gold Blend for around 20 years, I've managed to get 2 employers to change their coffee choice because it USED to be great (and they agreed at the time it was).  Now however there is no other way of putting it, it is terrible!  Black muck at the bottom of the cup, so weak that it doesn't even taste like coffee.  The only thing I can do is swap brands to something else unless you have the good sense and change it back to how it was.  I am not alone in the above opinion I have seen on several forums and social media sites ex-gold blend customers stating the same!!
Results.Title: What a total mess you have made of my coffee!!

ClientResponses.Response:
Hi, thanks very much for letting us know your thoughts on the new recipe. We really appreciate your feedback! The residue you can see at the bottom of your cup is micro ground coffee that was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend during the recent change. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee!

The difference between NESCAFÉ Gold Blend & NESCAFÉ Gold Barista style is down to the profile of each one! NESCAFÉ Gold Blend is rich & smooth, versus the more intense overall, full bodied profile of NESCAFÉ Gold Barista Style.

We'll certainly make a note of your comments & will be passing them to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText: Nescafe Gold Blend has been the leading brand of instant coffee for years - so why change it? Your new blend smells different, tastes different and leaves residue at the bottom of the cup. I have heard that you are trying to give it a more 'Barista' style - but why/ You already make Nescafe Barista..so if people actually want Barista style, they will pick one of your other brands. Sadly, as you do not have any other type of coffee, that tastes as smooth and mild as the 'original' Nescafe Gold Blend, I will have to find another brand. This will be very hard, as I have tried almost all of the other brands and types and nothing has come close to the taste of the original Gold Blend..... But, sadly, you leave me no choice.
Results.Title: Why change a winner?

Results.ReviewText: I usually make my own coffee using a machine however I often have a cup of instant for a change. I often buy Nescafe Gold Blend as I like the taste however am quite disappointed with the new offering. The change of jar shape doesn’t really bother me but it definitely doesn’t stand out as much as before as it just looks like all the other jars now. The coffee tastes much weaker than the original but the biggest change is the dregs left in bottom of the mug. Sorry but not nice at all. I’ll persevere til the end of the jar but at present am not convinced I’ll keep buying it.

Results.ReviewText: Hubby thought I had gone and bought a cheapo Gold Blend substitute when he saw the new branded packaging.  "No" said I "its the new fancy packaging" Happy Hubby made me a cuppa and delivered it to my hand.  Sip..."mmm...tastes strong"...Sip...."oooh thats a bit weird.  I think the milk has gone off".....Sip....."Errk, the milk has gone off"...Goes to sniff milk "the milk is fine"....Sip...."It's the coffee, i think it's the coffee.  The coffee is off"....Sip, Grimace...."Yes, its definitely the coffee"   Go to google...."See, it's not just me ...they've messed with the coffee" Goodbye Gold Blend, we shared some good times but it's over.  I need a new love, you've changed and I just don't like the new you.  I'm sure there's someone out there for us both.  Let's raise a cup to the old times.  PS please, let me know if you go back to being the old you....i'll be back in a shot  x
